President Cyril Ramaphosa is vowing to create jobs. He says he's concerned about the high levels of unemployment in the country. He was speaking at the launch of the Letsema campaign in Mangaung. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 MANGAUNG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is vowing to create jobs. He says he is concerned about the high levels of unemployment in the country. Ramaphosa says government is working hard to restructure the economy to create jobs. READ: WATCH | President visits troubled Mangaung Metro He was speaking at the launch of the Letsema campaign in Mangaung on Saturday. Meanwhile Ramaphosa has also conceded that service delivery is a major problem in Mangaung. However, he is promising to change that. Watch the video above for more details on this story.